description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a registered Mental Health Nurse to join a skilled and experienced specialist eating disorders team. This vacancy has arisen as a result of internal promotion of the previous postholder. The team has Nursing staff at A4C Bands 5,6 and 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a truly excellent opportunity for an enthusiastic mental health nurse to really enhance their clinical skills within a well established and skilled specialist team. We do not expect candidates to have in depth skills or knowledge in Eating Disorders (although this would be an advantage) but this is an excellent opportunity to develop your existing knowledge and skills. Adult eating Disorders Services are undergoing increased investment in staffing and training and the successful candidate will be part of this process. If you are an enthusiastic and passionate clinician interested in this fascinating and rewarding speciality then we would also love to hear from you and will provide training and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be well supported and supervised by a senior nursing colleague and ongoing training and group supervision will be provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
